    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>The for-mer anti-apartheid campaigner and cleric Allan Boesak was released from prison after serving a year and seven days of a three-year sentence. Mr. Boesak, former head of the Geneva-based World Alliance of Reformed Churches, was convicted of stealing thousands of dollars given by foreign donors meant to help needy children and educate black voters.</p>
        <p>Rachel L. Swarns (NYT)</p>
      </block>
